1
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:13,000
<i>I heard from Roman that he knows
someone who's an IED supplier.</i>

2
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:14,400
<i>He said he's planting it
himself.</i>

3
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:16,800
<i>He's heading to Mayor Guerrero's
political rally.</i>

4
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,267
<i> I need your help, Enriquez.</i>

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:21,767
<i>I saw him. His shirt
said RS Flower Supply.</i>

6
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:23,667
<i>The bombs might be hidden
in the flowers.</i>

7
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:24,567
<i>- Faye!
- Who are you?</i>

8
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,000
<i> Sir, you have to leave now.</i>

9
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,400
<i> There's a bomb threat.</i>

10
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:29,733
<i>Sir Tonyo, the bombs are in
the plants on stage!</i>

11
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:33,600
<i>Everyone evacuate the area now
because there's a bomb!</i>

12
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:37,367
<i> Mayor, you have a wound!</i>

13
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,667
<i>Let's get out of here now!
Hurry!</i>

14
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:43,667
<i>This horrendous act has no place
in our community.</i>

15
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,367
<i>Did you come here to make sure
that my dad's dead?</i>

16
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,733
<i>Glen, I had nothing to do
with this!</i>

17
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:49,900
<i> Then who?</i>

18
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:52,833
<i>Actually, it was Glen
who warned us about it.</i>

19
00:00:52,967 --> 00:00:55,533
<i>Sergeant Enriquez,
thank you so much.</i>

20
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,467
<i>They said you brought
my dad here.</i>

21
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,233
<i> You saved both of us.</i>

22
00:00:59,367 --> 00:01:00,433
<i> Why are you here?</i>

23
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:02,833
<i>They said you were at the rally
when the bomb exploded.</i>

24
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:04,533
<i>We were just leaving.
Come on, let's go.</i>

25
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:05,700
<i> Dad, wait.</i>

26
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,267
<i>Did you have something to do
with what happened?</i>

27
00:01:11,067 --> 00:01:12,200
Tonyo, son.

28
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,600
Do you really believe that
I had something to do with it?

29
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:15,033
I need to hear it from you.

30
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:17,633
Because I have reason
to believe you did.

31
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,100
Reason? What reason?

32
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:20,900
You gave Roman orders,
didn't you?

33
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:22,633
I asked what you told Roman
to do,

34
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:24,167
and you didn't want to say.

35
00:01:24,733 --> 00:01:26,833
So I followed him.

36
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:31,100
And wouldn't you know,
he went straight to the rally.

37
00:01:31,233 --> 00:01:33,733
Tonyo, I understand...

38
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:38,633
Dad, whatever happens,
you are my father.

39
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,267
I'm your son.

40
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:44,067
That's why I want to know...

41
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,933
did you tell Roman...

42
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:50,000
to plant that bomb?

43
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:58,000
As I said, I understand...

44
00:01:58,133 --> 00:02:01,733
why you'd think
the worst of me.

45
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:04,533
But I never gave
that kind of order.

46
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:10,300
Then what did you
order Roman to do?

47
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:13,133
I asked him to withdraw a large
amount of money from the bank.

48
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:17,000
I needed it to pay
my supporters

49
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:20,667
registered in Calabari
but living elsewhere.

50
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,533
Some of them are still
in the provinces.

51
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:25,633
I'm bringing them back
to vote for me.

52
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:30,533
Son, Joaquin is my friend.

53
00:02:30,667 --> 00:02:32,367
I'm close to his family.

54
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,933
I could never kill someone,

55
00:02:35,067 --> 00:02:37,467
just to win as Mayor.

56
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:23,433
Is Boss here, Sir?

57
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:25,367
Have you spoken to him?

58
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,300
Yes, but I'll tell you
more later about it.

59
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:30,300
Right now, we need
to speak with the Major.

60
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,767
Lieutenant Conde,
Sergeant Enriquez.

61
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,900
Councilor.

62
00:03:35,033 --> 00:03:36,033
Thank you. Thank you.

63
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:39,367
Thank you for saving my dad
and acting on instinct.

64
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,367
Just doing our job,
Councilor.

65
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,200
Yeah, but you did
a really good job.

66
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:47,467
You two, you really are the
pride of Police Station 12.

67
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:53,033
And I believe you'll catch,
whoever's behind this.

68
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:55,200
What I want you to know
is that...

69
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,633
I'm on your side.

70
00:03:57,767 --> 00:03:59,267
I'm willing to extend help

71
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:02,400
in order to lessen the criminal
activities here in our area,

72
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:05,467
especially if someone powerful
is behind it.

73
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:09,567
But what if the person behind it
is close to you, Councilor?

74
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,667
He should pay even more.

75
00:04:12,633 --> 00:04:15,700
There are no relatives
in the eyes of the law....

76
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,900
even godfathers.

77
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:21,433
So, I'll go ahead.

78
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:23,833
If you need anything,
just let me know.

79
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:25,667
- Thank you, really.
- Okay, Sir.

80
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,867
Thank you.

81
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,333
Let's go.

82
00:04:34,367 --> 00:04:36,167
<i> Hey, Boss! That's enough!</i>

83
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,567
<i> Stop! That's enough!</i>

84
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,900
<i>Did you come here to make sure
my dad's dead?</i>

85
00:04:41,667 --> 00:04:44,500
This is the first time
I've seen Glen like this.

86
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:47,867
I hope he didn't hold back.

87
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,400
Not funny, Joaquin.

88
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:53,500
Violence is still unacceptable.

89
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,333
I know, I know.

90
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:56,767
I'm just proud of him.

91
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:59,600
That's all. That's all for me.

92
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,600
You're proud of him?

93
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:04,400
But not proud enough
to be your running mate?

94
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,900
There you go again, Sofia.

95
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:11,400
I told you, I have reasons.

96
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:14,367
First, he's not ready.

97
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,600
- What?
- Yes.

98
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,800
How can he not be ready?

99
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:21,433
You saw how he stood up for you.

100
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:26,233
Sofia, he punched Victor
in front of the press

101
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:29,600
to look good

102
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:33,233
and to make himself seem
like a good son.

103
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:34,933
Joaquin...

104
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:37,400
Sofia, that's enough.

105
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,967
I want to rest.

106
00:05:57,467 --> 00:05:58,500
Hello.

107
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:03,267
Hello.

108
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,467
You don't remember me?

109
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:10,000
Sorry, a lot has happened today.

110
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:12,467
Okay, it's fine.

111
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:14,967
I'm Vince.

112
00:06:16,733 --> 00:06:18,100
Supporter of your dad.

113
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,933
- Thank you.
- So how is he?

114
00:06:22,067 --> 00:06:23,767
Is he okay now?

115
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,267
Faye...

116
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:27,100
who are you talking to?

117
00:06:28,633 --> 00:06:30,000
I remember you.

118
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:31,433
You're the one who helped us

119
00:06:31,567 --> 00:06:33,800
to get out before
the bomb went off, right?

120
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:35,867
- Yes, Sir.
- That was you.

121
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,000
Yes, yes. I remember.

122
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:40,933
Thank you so much.

123
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,433
It's nothing, Ma'am.

124
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:43,933
Thank you.

125
00:06:44,067 --> 00:06:45,200
It's nothing, Sir.

126
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:48,633
But don't worry,
we'll give you a reward.

127
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:50,067
- A reward, Sir?
- Yes.

128
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:52,800
Sir...

129
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:54,067
if you're giving me a reward,

130
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:56,833
maybe it could be
a job instead?

131
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:59,067
Any kind of job,
I can do it.

132
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,133
I can do a lot of things.

133
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:08,367
<i> Joaquin is my friend.</i>

134
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,900
<i> I'm close to his family.</i>

135
00:07:10,033 --> 00:07:13,200
<i>I could never kill
just to win as mayor.</i>

136
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,200
What do you think?

137
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:19,300
That Boss guy is lying,
Chief.

138
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:20,700
He's too much.

139
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,533
He's trying too hard
to convince Sir Tonyo

140
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:24,100
that he's a good guy.

141
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:27,300
You, Conde? What do you think?

142
00:07:28,367 --> 00:07:29,400
Sir...

143
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,800
it's just an audio recording,

144
00:07:30,933 --> 00:07:33,133
but he was different when
I was face-to-face with him.

145
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:34,833
You can tell from
someone's body language

146
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:36,567
when they're lying.

147
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:39,967
I think he was sincere
when he said this.

148
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,533
Sincere?

149
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:45,233
Sir, hold on.
You're being sensitive now?

150
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:47,933
What is this,
blood ties talking?

151
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,233
Enriquez...

152
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:52,467
I've got a strong feeling
that he's telling the truth.

153
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:55,867
Let's say Boss had nothing
to do with it...

154
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,333
but then who did it?

155
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:05,500
Only Roman can answer that.

156
00:08:05,633 --> 00:08:09,200
Didn't you hear him
order the IED?

157
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,867
And Boss said,

158
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,533
he asked Roman to go
to the bank.

159
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:16,733
So let's get
the bank's CCTV footage

160
00:08:16,867 --> 00:08:19,900
to see if Boss was telling
the truth.

161
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,833
Conde...

162
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,733
didn't Lara used to work there?

163
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:26,067
Do you still have
a contact at the bank?

164
00:08:33,367 --> 00:08:36,267
Roman, my dad got caught
in the blast.

165
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,467
What happened?

166
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:41,033
Sorry, Boss.

167
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:43,967
I think I used a strong bomb.

168
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,767
But wait...

169
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,800
Isn't it better that the Mayor
got caught in the blast?

170
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:51,300
But that wasn't the plan.

171
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:53,367
You know me, Roman.

172
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,533
I don't go off-plan.

173
00:08:55,700 --> 00:09:00,267
When I say a small blast,
I mean small blast only!

174
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:06,133
Yes, Boss.

175
00:09:06,267 --> 00:09:07,933
I'm really sorry.

176
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:26,500
Boss?

177
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:29,233
Roman, change of plans.

178
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:32,333
I think Vice Mayor Del Mundo
overheard us.

179
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:35,233
Kill her. Use your guys.

180
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:38,733
Do it before she says anything.

181
00:09:38,867 --> 00:09:40,367
Yes, Boss.

182
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:52,667
Ma'am Jane.

183
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,033
Antonio.

184
00:09:55,167 --> 00:09:57,033
Sorry, I made you come here
instead.

185
00:09:57,167 --> 00:09:59,933
We had a bank conference here
earlier.

186
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:01,567
How are you?

187
00:10:01,733 --> 00:10:03,100
It's been a while.

188
00:10:03,233 --> 00:10:04,800
Yes.

189
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:06,967
Oh, well...

190
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:09,367
sometimes, I'm okay, but...

191
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,967
mostly not.

192
00:10:12,433 --> 00:10:14,067
What can I help you with?

193
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,500
Do you need a loan?
I'll take care of it.

194
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:18,800
You know I'm close to Lara

195
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:22,133
and I wouldn't want her thinking
I don't look out for you.

196
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:25,133
It's not about a loan.

197
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:33,100
I need your bank's CCTV footage.

198
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:36,133
I'm investigating someone

199
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,900
and I need to confirm

200
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:41,767
if he's really there
at the bank that time.

201
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:45,400
Sure, just text me
the date and time.

202
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:49,733
So, I'll go ahead.

203
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:52,700
I'll just message you
when I get the file.

204
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:55,033
Thank you so much,
Ma'am Jane.

205
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:14,000
- Boss.
- Oh, Vice.

206
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,833
What do we need to talk about

207
00:11:23,967 --> 00:11:26,500
that you can't say
on the phone?

208
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:31,833
Roman De Leon!

209
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,367
Oh, Boss Ma'am,
Boss Sir...

210
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,600
what can I do for you?

211
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:40,600
We're inviting you to the
precinct for questioning

212
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:42,067
about the explosion
that occurred

213
00:11:42,233 --> 00:11:44,100
at the political rally
of Mayor Joaquin Guerrero.

214
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:46,300
Wait, wait. Am I a suspect?

215
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:48,033
No.

216
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:49,567
Not yet.

217
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:52,133
We just want to talk to you.

218
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:54,467
And who's the person
who told you that

219
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,833
I should be questioned
about those things?

220
00:11:57,967 --> 00:12:00,500
Of course, we can't say who.

221
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:03,667
What if I don't agree?

222
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,733
So what if you can't say no?

223
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:08,000
What if we end up fighting?

224
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:13,100
We're not afraid of you.

225
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:15,633
There are two of us
police officers here.

226
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:23,900
Be careful with what you say
and do.

227
00:12:24,433 --> 00:12:25,900
We just want to talk to you.

228
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,700
That's the problem.
I don't want to talk.

229
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,567
Is there anything you can do?

230
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:33,433
Are you trying to bully us?

231
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:35,000
Relax, Boss Man.

232
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,900
Relax, easy.

233
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:40,267
All I'm looking for
is a warrant.

234
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,267
Let's go, Enriquez.

235
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:46,133
We're not going to get anything
out of this guy.

236
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:47,133
Wait, Sir.

237
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,367
Is that it?

238
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:51,000
He can't even answer
our questions.

239
00:12:51,633 --> 00:12:52,633
Don't worry.

240
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:56,233
We'll get back to this guy
when we have a warrant.

241
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:58,500
And I'm right here, waiting.

242
00:12:58,633 --> 00:13:00,500
Let's go, Enriquez.

243
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:15,000
Are you still waiting
for someone?

244
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:17,433
None.

245
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,433
Excuse me.

246
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:30,833
Housekeeping, Ma'am.

247
00:13:30,967 --> 00:13:32,600
Can you just go back,
Mister, please?

248
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:34,267
Ma'am, I'll just go get
the trash, Ma'am.

249
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,200
Later.

250
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:37,733
I need it. I'm going
to get scolded.

251
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,167
Leslie, what does he need?

252
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,867
He said he needed
to take out the trash.

253
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:52,333
Trash?

254
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:57,267
Oh, it'll only be a moment.

255
00:13:58,533 --> 00:13:59,267
Boss!

256
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:01,567
- Boss! Boss!
- Shut up!

257
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,667
Mess up the table
like there was a fight.

258
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,300
Mess it up! Hurry up!

259
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:13,033
Put that in your mouth,
hurry up!

260
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:18,700
Put that in your mouth,
hurry up!

261
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,433
Hurry up!

262
00:14:20,567 --> 00:14:22,067
Come here.

263
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,167
Scratch him.

264
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:24,400
Hurry up!

265
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:28,933
Quick!

266
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:37,067
One more! Scratch him harder!
Go on!

267
00:14:39,667 --> 00:14:41,267
One more, scratch harder!

268
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:47,667
Stand up! Stand up!

269
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,967
Hey, is that Boss?

270
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:13,800
Yes, that's Boss.

271
00:15:13,933 --> 00:15:15,700
He looks guilty about
the explosion that happened.

272
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:18,033
He doesn't seem affected.

273
00:15:23,067 --> 00:15:24,500
Excuse me.

274
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:28,833
I heard you saw Boss?

275
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:33,133
I'm his bodyguard.

276
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:36,667
He sent me here earlier, but...

277
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,867
I don't know where to find him.

278
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,100
Oh, yes, I recognize you.

279
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:42,367
You're the ones who saved him

280
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:45,067
from the one who wanted
to stab him.

281
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,700
That's right.

282
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,433
Can you take me to him?

283
00:15:51,567 --> 00:15:54,200
He might get mad at me,
I'm late already.

284
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:56,667
Okay, this way.

285
00:16:22,867 --> 00:16:24,533
Here, Sir.

286
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:32,633
Why is this open?

287
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,567
You killed the Vice Mayor!

288
00:16:41,733 --> 00:16:43,267
No, I didn't do it!

289
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,667
Put down your gun!

290
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:50,367
Put down your gun.

291
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:52,267
- I didn't do it.
- Put down your gun!

292
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:53,867
I didn't do this!

293
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,067
I was just framed!

294
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,667
- Raise your hand!
- My son, my son...

295
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,167
- I said hand's up!
- What?

296
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,667
Leslie and I talked.

297
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:00,633
After that...

298
00:17:00,767 --> 00:17:02,267
Just explain yourself
at the precinct.

299
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,233
Someone hit me in the back,
and then, I don't know anymore.

300
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:07,100
I saw her dead
when I woke up!

301
00:17:07,233 --> 00:17:09,000
Sir, I'm going
to call the police!

302
00:17:09,133 --> 00:17:10,767
Miss...

303
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:14,667
I'm a police officer.

304
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,433
You're still a police officer?

305
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,800
Aren't you fired already?

306
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:21,167
I'm an undercover police.

307
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,067
- But...
- Wear that!

308
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:31,467
- I didn't kill Leslie!
- I said wear that!

309
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:36,900
I got to hand it to you, Son.

310
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,600
You're already learning
the ropes.

311
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:47,700
For sure, your image
to the press is good.

312
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:49,967
Dad, I didn't do that

313
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:52,533
to improve my image
to the press.

314
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,633
Okay.

315
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,433
- Joaquin.
- Oh?

316
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:03,200
It's Major.

317
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:06,733
Hello, Major?

318
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,633
How's the investigation going?

319
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,233
What?

320
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:16,167
My God!

321
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:18,467
She was just here earlier.

322
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:22,833
Are you sure?

323
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,100
Okay, let me know.

324
00:18:27,033 --> 00:18:28,833
Okay.

325
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:34,500
Dad...

326
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:36,200
what happened?

327
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:39,567
Vice Mayor Leslie Del Mundo...

328
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:42,967
got murdered.

329
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:44,233
Huh?

330
00:18:44,367 --> 00:18:45,767
Yes.

331
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,500
The suspect...

332
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:50,433
is Victor.

333
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,533
But she was just here...

334
00:19:10,667 --> 00:19:12,167
Tonyo...

335
00:19:13,533 --> 00:19:16,567
I accept it if people lose
trust in me.

336
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:19,667
But my own son?

337
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:23,933
I also accept that there
are many murderers...

338
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:29,233
but not my own father.

339
00:19:40,467 --> 00:19:43,067
Roman's record seems clean.

340
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:48,267
We need to find probable cause,
so we can bring Roman here.

341
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:50,700
Ma'am Enriquez!

342
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:53,500
Lieutenant Conde is here
with Boss.

343
00:20:14,233 --> 00:20:15,133
Boss...

344
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:18,233
Follow me to my office.

345
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:23,833
Stay here, Noble.

346
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:36,567
Sir, we've already taken Boss
to the cell.

347
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:43,700
It's better if nothing comes out
in the media...

348
00:20:44,433 --> 00:20:46,200
until our investigation
is complete.

349
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:50,100
Chief, what about
the Vice Mayor's family?

350
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,033
I'll take care of that, Garcia.

351
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:55,733
Conde, go back to the hotel.

352
00:20:55,867 --> 00:20:57,967
Maybe we can get
some more evidence.

353
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,067
Yes, Sir.

354
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:05,367
The Mayor is calling.

355
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:10,733
Hello, Mayor?

356
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:13,633
Okay.

357
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,000
The Mayor is here.

358
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:27,533
Good evening, Mayor.

359
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:29,367
Good evening, Major.

360
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,867
Oh, Mayor.

361
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,967
There should be no press
until the investigation is over.

362
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,767
No, Major!

363
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,900
Lieutenant Conde...

364
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:45,233
you said you went into
the private room of the hotel,

365
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:49,500
and saw Victor holding a gun,

366
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:52,867
and Vice Mayor Del Mundo
lying on the ground.

367
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,567
Am I right or wrong?

368
00:21:56,433 --> 00:21:57,367
You're right, Mayor.

369
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,533
Well, that's right!

370
00:21:59,667 --> 00:22:01,567
The people of Calabari
needs to know,

371
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:02,800
who the real suspect is

372
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:06,300
in the murder of
Vice Mayor Del Mundo.

373
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:08,333
- Glen!
- Dad.

374
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:09,700
Call the press.

375
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:11,733
We're having a press conference.

376
00:22:11,867 --> 00:22:13,500
Okay.

377
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:32,233
Earlier, I heard
from Major Flores...

378
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:40,233
that someone killed our beloved
Vice Mayor Leslie Del Mundo.

379
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:44,333
Although, the loss of Vice Mayor
Leslie Del Mundo

380
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:47,600
was painful to all of us...

381
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:51,767
I want you all to know...

382
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:56,500
that the suspect who killed her
has been caught.

383
00:22:59,133 --> 00:23:00,967
He is none other than...

384
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:04,633
Victor Santiago!

385
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:29,800
Victor...

386
00:23:31,233 --> 00:23:33,467
I didn't think
you could do this!

387
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:37,467
Is it because Vice Mayor Leslie
sided with me?

388
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,300
Mayor...

389
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:42,300
be careful with your
investigation.

390
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:46,367
Make sure no one interferes.

391
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:50,567
I believe the truth
will come out.

392
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:52,600
Go ahead, lock him up!

393
00:23:52,733 --> 00:23:55,233
Mayor! Mayor!

394
00:23:58,667 --> 00:24:00,200
<i> How did it happen, Mayor?</i>

395
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:05,367
Sir, do you think this is what
we've been waiting for?

396
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,200
I don't know, Enriquez.

397
00:24:34,067 --> 00:24:35,233
Ms. Britney!

398
00:24:35,367 --> 00:24:36,533
You're shameless!

399
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:37,767
You're a murderer!

400
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:38,700
What?

401
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:39,700
Who did you kill?

402
00:24:39,833 --> 00:24:41,333
We've thought
of a sting operation.

403
00:24:41,467 --> 00:24:43,200
Someone will pose
as a potential victim.

404
00:24:43,333 --> 00:24:44,733
The moment the criminal
makes a move,

405
00:24:44,867 --> 00:24:45,900
we'll arrest them.

406
00:24:46,033 --> 00:24:47,033
I'm telling you,

407
00:24:47,167 --> 00:24:49,967
if our mission got compromised
because of you,

408
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:52,167
I'll make sure
you get suspended.

409
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:54,033
Pervert!

410
00:24:56,467 --> 00:24:58,467
Are you and Sergeant Enriquez
dating?

411
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:00,333
We just work together.

412
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,267
But just a warning,
she's mean in person.

413
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:08,567
That's what I want,
a challenge.

414
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:13,967
You think that's what
I'm going to do?
